genresAdvancedInfo.name: rock campineiro
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Rock campineiro is a subgenre of rock music that originated in the Campinas region of Brazil. It is characterized by its upbeat tempo and catchy melodies, often featuring lyrics about love and relationships. The instrumentation typically includes electric guitars, drums, and keyboards, and the music often incorporates elements of pop and funk.
